Why not something like this?<p><pre><code>    function routine () {
      doIOForMe(function (resp) {
        doMoreIO(resp, function (nextResp) {
          transform(nextResp)
        })
      })
    }

    // or with a little helper function:

    function routine () {
      chainTogether
        ( doIOForMe
        , doMoreIO
        , transform
        )
    }
</code></pre>
The "Step" library from Tim Caswell (creationix) lets you do a LOT of very interesting parallel/serial stuff.  In npm, I have a few helper functions that make it easy to do serial "this then that" stuff.<p>It would be nice to have something in the language that does this.  Maybe something for the Coffeescript guys to check out.  For me, plain old JavaScript is enough, I guess.
